Program: Discovery
Title: The Galaxy's New Black Hole
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwj8
Last Broadcast Date: 16 October 1995
The discovery of a new black hole, a collapsed star which can swallow light. Scientists discovered the black hole in our galaxy by examining the x ray outburst coming from it. Also in the programme, the plant that flowers to order and the discovery of new atoms.